## Tools Used 

- Burp Suite Community Edition.
- FoxyProxy browser extension.
- Built‑in Burp Chromium browser.

## Findings

- Burp Suite is the industry standard for web application penetration testing.
- Community Edition covers manual testing essentials.
- Proper setup (proxy, HTTPS interception, scoping) is critical for effective use.

## Mitigation / Best Practices

- Always define scope to avoid testing unintended targets.
- Secure Burp’s CA certificate to prevent misuse.
- Use Repeater for controlled testing, not live exploitation.
- Upgrade to Professional for automation when needed.

## Conclusion

- Establish the foundation of Burp Suite usage.
- Understanding proxy interception, navigation, scoping, and HTTPS handling is essential for web security testing.
- This knowledge prepares you for advanced Burp Suite labs and real‑world penetration testing.
